1
00:00:01,080 --> 00:00:03,447
我生来便是英格兰的郡长
(UHTRED) I was born an ealdorman of England.

2
00:00:03,760 --> 00:00:06,843
诺森布里亚贝班堡领地的正统继承人
True heir to the Northumbrian lands of Bebbanburg.

3
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:09,526
我十二岁第一次上战场
I was 12 years old when I Hrst went to war.

4
00:00:09,680 --> 00:00:11,409
亲眼看着父亲战死
I saw my father killed.

5
00:00:12,200 --> 00:00:16,285
我和撒克逊女孩布丽达被入侵者掳走 
Stolen by the invaders, along with the Saxon girl Brida,

6
00:00:16,440 --> 00:00:20,490
我先做了奴隶，后来成了拉格纳伯爵的养子
I became Hrst a slave, and then a son to Earl Ragnar.

7
00:00:21,480 --> 00:00:24,450
命运让我变成了丹麦人
Fate had made me a Dane.

8
00:00:24,880 --> 00:00:29,044
命运让小拉格纳成了我兄弟, 让布丽达成了我的爱人
It made Young Rag/var my brother, and Bride my lover.

9
00:00:29,880 --> 00:00:33,123
- 而后命运带来了背叛 - 着火了!
- And then fate brought betrayal. - Fire!

10
00:00:34,320 --> 00:00:35,651


11
00:00:35,800 --> 00:00:38,644
谣言四起, 说是我杀了拉格纳
Lies were thrown to the wind saying I had killed Ragnar.

12
00:00:38,800 --> 00:00:42,247]
我们带着他藏的财物, 一路往南
(UHTRED) So taking his hidden wealth, we fled south...

13
00:00:44,120 --> 00:00:46,600
逃向威塞克斯, 逃向贝奥卡
To Wessex, to Beocca,

14
00:00:46,760 --> 00:00:49,047
逃向国王的兄弟阿尔弗雷德
and to the king's brother Alfred.

15
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:53,285
丹麦人把我当撒克逊人, 撒克逊人把我当丹麦人
Seen by the Danes as a Saxon and by Saxons as a Dane,

16
00:00:53,440 --> 00:00:55,966
没有人信我的话
my word could not be trusted.

17
00:00:56,120 --> 00:00:58,327
但我是乌特雷德, 乌特雷德之子
But I am Uhtred, son of Uhtred,

18
00:00:59,040 --> 00:01:00,883
命运主宰一切
and destiny is all.

19
00:01:41,080 --> 00:01:42,844
- 让开路 - 闪开! 是国王!
- (MAN) Clear the way. - Stand clear! It is the king!

20
00:01:43,840 --> 00:01:46,286
大人, 我必须说, 那斧子砍得很深
(ODDA) I have to speak, lord. The axe cut deep.

21
00:01:46,440 --> 00:01:50,161
- 就算是国王也撑不住 - 我们祈祷, 静待结果
- Even a king couldn't survive. - We shall pray and we shall see.

22
00:02:13,760 --> 00:02:16,081

23
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:18,611
大人, 抱歉
Apologies, lord,

24
00:02:18,760 --> 00:02:22,048
在没有事先和阿尔佛雷德商量之前, 我只能做这么多了
this was the best I could do without first speaking to Alfred.

25
00:02:22,200 --> 00:02:24,521
我带来了食物和麦酒
I have brought food and ale,

26
00:02:24,680 --> 00:02:27,923
- 更重要的是, 有好消息 - 阿尔弗雷德死了?
,- and more importantly, good news. - Alfred is dead?

27
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:32,004
恰恰相反, 他活着, 而且赢了
The opposite. He is alive and he is victorious.

28
00:02:32,160 --> 00:02:34,686
我们击败了丹麦人
We defeated the Danes.

29
00:02:34,880 --> 00:02:36,564


30
00:02:36,720 --> 00:02:39,485
- 这算什么好消息？- 阿尔弗雷德采纳了你的建议
- Why is this good news? - Alfred acted upon your advice.

31
00:02:39,640 --> 00:02:42,166
- 你也分享了他的荣耀 - 荣耀？
- You share in his glory. - (BRIDA) Glory?

32
00:02:43,040 --> 00:02:45,850
那他为什么被关在笼子里，只能蹲在角落里解手？
Then why is he caged and left to shit in the corner?

33
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,445
你管这叫荣耀？
You call that glory?

34
00:02:47,600 --> 00:02:49,011
她就不能闭一会儿嘴吗？
Can she not hold her tongue for just one moment?

35
00:02:49,160 --> 00:02:52,801
不，她不能，也不会！
No she cannot and she will not!

36
00:02:52,960 --> 00:02:55,167
- 把你的食物留着！- 只有阿尔弗雷德
- Keep your food! - (BEOCCA) Only Alfred

37
00:02:55,320 --> 00:02:58,722
- 我不吃也不喝！- 只有阿尔弗雷德能下令放你
- (BRIDA) I will not eat or drink! - Only Alfred can order your release.

38
00:02:58,880 --> 00:03:00,325
我去跟他谈
I will speak with him.

39
00:03:00,480 --> 00:03:03,689
姑娘，你应该趁这段时间好好反省一下自己
You should spend this time, girl, to contemplate improvement.

40
00:03:03,840 --> 00:03:07,447
我要用这段时间来诅咒你
I will use this time to curse you.

41
00:03:07,600 --> 00:03:10,729
- 那就诅咒吧 - 阿尔弗雷德拒绝了我的效忠
- Then do it. - Alfred refused my sword.

42
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:15,367
除非他来求我，否则我不会再开口
I won't be offering it again unless he begs.

43
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:17,682
大人，我怀疑你这股倔劲
Lord, I wonder whether your pig-headedness

44
00:03:17,840 --> 00:03:19,604
不过是蠢到家了
is not simple stupidity.

45
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:23,367
等他把铠甲上的泥和血刮干净，就会派人来找你
He'll send for you when he has scraped the mud and blood from his mail.

46
00:03:23,520 --> 00:03:26,171
我们要向奥丁感恩，感谢他护佑我们
(BRIDA) We will give thanks to Odin for our deliverance.

47
00:03:26,320 --> 00:03:28,129
你这么做吧
(BEOCCA) Do that.

48
00:03:28,440 --> 00:03:30,124
我们是丹麦人！
(BRIDA) We are Danes!

49
00:03:31,160 --> 00:03:32,685
放尊重点
(GUARD) Show respect!

50
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:37,289
再来一次，我就割断你的喉咙
Do it again, and I will cut you cock to throat.

51
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:42,850


52
00:03:50,080 --> 00:03:51,923
你是威塞克斯的英雄
You are a hero of Wessex.

53
00:03:52,960 --> 00:03:55,088
恭喜你
Congratulations.

54
00:03:55,720 --> 00:03:57,563
我们还活着
We're alive.

55
00:03:59,640 --> 00:04:00,971

56
00:04:01,120 --> 00:04:02,884
什么事
(ALFRED) what is it?

57
00:04:04,960 --> 00:04:07,247
我等不及要见你
(AELSWITH) I couldn't wait to see you.

58
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:10,483
有人告诉我你平安无事, 但我要亲眼看到才放心
I was told you are safe, but I needed proof.

59
00:04:12,120 --> 00:04:13,963
现在看到了
Here it is.

60
00:04:16,200 --> 00:04:18,407
- 你们都退下, 我妻子来帮我 - 是, 大人
-Leave us. My wife will help me. -My lord.

61
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:24,242
这是我的荣幸
My privilege.

62
00:04:27,440 --> 00:04:30,523
把它好好修补, 仔细点
Ensure it is repaired, and well.

63
00:04:31,280 --> 00:04:33,965
没有你我就是个不知所措的傻瓜
I'd be a lost fool without you.

64
00:04:38,680 --> 00:04:41,411
哈, 笨手笨脚的
Heh. Fingers and thumbs.

65
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:49,571


66
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:51,844
谁在敲门?
Who knocks?

67
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:53,650
大人
(BEOCCA) My lord.

68
00:04:53,920 --> 00:04:56,571
夫人, 打扰了
My lady. Forgive me.

69
00:04:56,720 --> 00:04:59,883
我想趁这会儿谈谈郡长乌特雷德的事
I was, hoping for a moment to discuss the Ealdorman Uhtred.

70
00:05:00,040 --> 00:05:02,725
神父, 恕我直言, 大人需要休息了
Father, forgive me, but my lord is in need of rest.

71
00:05:04,280 --> 00:05:05,611
确实
He is.

72
00:05:05,760 --> 00:05:07,524
你也需要休息...
You are, um...

73
00:05:08,720 --> 00:05:10,449
抱歉
Forgive me.

74
00:05:18,040 --> 00:05:21,249


75
00:05:25,320 --> 00:05:26,651
埃塞尔沃尔德
(YOUNGER) Aethelwold.

76
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:29,121
你在山岗上吗? 我没见到你
Were you on the hill? I didn't see you?

77
00:05:30,640 --> 00:05:34,440
我被留在神父那边, 没有上去
I was kept safe with the priests.

78
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:42,043
以后还有很多仗要打
There will be other battles, many.

79
00:05:42,200 --> 00:05:45,249
会没完没了的, 直到我们全死光为止
And on and on it will go, I'm sure, until we are all dead.

80
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:48,324
- 你是说我们该投降? - 绝不
- You saying we should surrender? - Never.

81
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:50,884
绝不
Never.

82
00:05:51,640 --> 00:05:54,086
但我并不反对妥协
But I am not against compromise.

83
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:57,767
我虽敬爱天主, 却不急着去见他
As much as I love my God, I am in no hurry to reach heaven.

84
00:05:58,160 --> 00:06:00,288
就算跪满一地的神父
I fear no number of kneeling clergy men

85
00:06:00,440 --> 00:06:03,444
也改变不了异教徒的斧头已经定下的结局
will change what a heathen's axe has already decreed.

86
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:06,444
我们该为国王的继承人祈祷
Our prayers should be with the king's successor.

87
00:06:09,320 --> 00:06:12,164
王冠是我的, 这是我与生俱来的权利
The crown is mine, my birth right.

88
00:06:13,560 --> 00:06:15,005
你有异议?
You disagree?

89
00:06:15,160 --> 00:06:17,561
有人会说您年纪太轻, 大人
The argument will be that you are young, lord.

90
00:06:17,720 --> 00:06:20,530
- 我是父亲的继承人 - 您是父亲的继承人,
- I am my father's heir. - You are your father's heir,

91
00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:23,126
但阿尔佛雷德是你父亲的兄弟
but your father was also bonded to Alfred.

92
00:06:25,040 --> 00:06:27,691
儿子比兄弟先
A son comes before a brother.

93
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:34,451
那您或许应该直接去找国王谈
Then perhaps you should speak to the king directly.

94
00:06:36,840 --> 00:06:38,729
我是这么想的, 大人,
'Tis my thinking, lord,

95
00:06:38,880 --> 00:06:42,601
若您父亲在临终前能亲口点名让您继位,
that if on his death bed your father were to name you as his successor,

96
00:06:42,760 --> 00:06:46,003
贤人会议就很难违逆他的意愿
the Witan would find it difficult to go against him.

97
00:06:46,160 --> 00:06:50,006
我相信您父亲会很乐意附在您耳边说那句话的,
I believe your father would only be too happy to whisper in your ear,

98
00:06:50,240 --> 00:06:52,891
不管他当时是否清醒
whether he was conscious or not.

99
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:59,527
你的建言我不会忘, 小奥达
Your counsel will not be forgotten, Young Odda.

100
00:07:00,880 --> 00:07:02,609
谢谢您, 大人
Thank you, lord.

101
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:16,125
古思伦, 你没等我就出兵了
(UBBA) Guthrum, you went into battle without me.

102
00:07:16,280 --> 00:07:17,770
为什么?
Why was that?

103
00:07:17,920 --> 00:07:19,445
那不是本来的打算
That was not the intention.

104
00:07:21,400 --> 00:07:23,289
是吗?
Is that so?

105
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:25,731
那为什么还是发生了?
Then why did it happen?

106
00:07:26,760 --> 00:07:29,809
- 进去说 - 就在这儿说
- Let's talk inside. - We will talk here.

107
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:33,007
他们出兵比我们预料的早,
They marched sooner than we expected,

108
00:07:33,160 --> 00:07:35,686
而且在山上占了好位置
and they positioned themselves well on the hill.

109
00:07:35,840 --> 00:07:38,650
- 这种事不会再发生 - 不会再发生了
- It will not happen again. - It will not happen again

110
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:40,928
因为你的人已经折损了一半
because you have lost half your men.

111
00:07:41,080 --> 00:07:43,651
我们杀了他们的国王，埃塞尔雷德
We killed their king, Aethelred.

112
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:48,204
- 你亲眼看见他倒下了？ - 是，我亲眼看见的,
- Did you see him fall? - Yeah, I saw him fall,

113
00:07:48,360 --> 00:07:50,931
一斧头劈下去，死透了
he took an axe. He's dead.

114
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:52,411
我们没有败
We were not beaten.

115
00:07:52,560 --> 00:07:55,848
哼，你想当威塞克斯国王，我可以允许
Hm. You want to become king of Wessex, I will allow that.

116
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:58,367
但我的报酬呢？我的银子？我的粮食？
But where is my payment? My silver? My grain?

117
00:07:58,520 --> 00:08:01,683
- 说好了给的，现在却没了 - 都还在那儿
- It was promised, but now it has gone. - It's still there.

118
00:08:01,840 --> 00:08:04,650
- 丹麦人不会输 - 我没有输
- Danes do not lose. - I am not lost.

119
00:08:04,800 --> 00:08:08,521
你给了他们希望，古思伦，这比输了还糟
You have given them hope, Guthrum, that is worse.

120
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:11,524
没了国王，他们就没有希望
Without the king, there is no hope.

121
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:23,010
如果他们真的打败了丹麦人，当然我不相信是真的，那他们为什么不开宴庆功？
If they've defeated the Danes, which I won't believe, why aren't they feasting?

122
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:25,208
那个神父没说谎,
The priest doesn't lie,

123
00:08:25,360 --> 00:08:27,647
尽管他只是个神父
despite him being a priest.

124
00:08:29,760 --> 00:08:31,967
他们为什么这么不一样？
Why are they so different?

125
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:34,720
- 这么愁眉苦脸 - 天主的旨意
- So miserable. - God's wish.

126
00:08:34,880 --> 00:08:36,245


127
00:08:38,120 --> 00:08:39,451
我不会变成一个撒克逊女人,
I won't become a Saxon woman,

128
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:41,568
我不要洗衣、下地干活干到累死，还要做饭
I won't wash, work the fields until I drop and cook.

129
00:08:41,720 --> 00:08:43,882
- 不会走到那一步的 - 那不会是我的日子
- It won't come to that. - That won't be my life.

130
00:08:44,040 --> 00:08:46,520
阿尔弗雷德能帮我们，我们可以利用他...
Alfred can help us. We'll use him...

131
00:08:46,680 --> 00:08:48,045


132
00:08:48,680 --> 00:08:52,401
先借他的地方落脚，再从他那儿捞财富
for shelter, and then for wealth.

133
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:58,286
- 他利用了你 - 现在他欠我的
- He has used you. - And now he owes me.

134
00:09:02,560 --> 00:09:04,403


135
00:09:06,120 --> 00:09:08,566


136
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:23,049
早上好
Good morning.

137
00:09:28,560 --> 00:09:30,927
谢谢你昨晚的款待
My thanks for last night.

138
00:09:35,840 --> 00:09:37,205


139
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:49,049
开门，我要见我父亲
Open the door, I wish to see my father.

140
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:55,722
开门，否则我割下你的蛋蛋当弹弓用
Open the door, or I'll have your balls for sling-shot.

141
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:58,204
埃塞尔沃尔德
Aethelwold.

142
00:09:58,360 --> 00:10:01,011
我来为父亲祈祷，陪在他身边
I am here to pray for my father, to be at his side.

143
00:10:01,160 --> 00:10:03,208
国王已经驾崩了
The king is dead.

144
00:10:05,240 --> 00:10:07,129
为何没人来叫我？我本应陪在他身边的
Why was I not called? I should have been at his side.

145
00:10:07,320 --> 00:10:11,245
- 找不到你 - 我就在自己的寝室里睡觉
- You could not be found. - I was sleeping in my chamber.

146
00:10:28,880 --> 00:10:30,564


147
00:10:40,920 --> 00:10:45,209
国王临终前，指定我为王位继承人
Before he passed, the king named me as heir to the throne.

148
00:10:48,600 --> 00:10:50,250
他亲口告诉我的
That's what he told me.

149
00:10:50,880 --> 00:10:52,769
这是实情
It's the truth.

150
00:10:53,560 --> 00:10:55,369
这是他最后的心愿
His last wish.

151
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:58,287
这是他最后的旨意
His last command.

152
00:10:59,160 --> 00:11:02,482
你们最好都把这话传出去
You would all do well to repeat this.

153
00:11:07,760 --> 00:11:10,240
我会将你的主张禀报贤人会议
I'll inform the Witan of your claim.

154
00:11:11,080 --> 00:11:14,482
- 你应该这么做 - 不过在场所有人，还有更多人，
- You should. - Although each person here, and more,

155
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:17,849
都亲耳听见你父亲将王冠传给了阿尔弗雷德
heard your father bequeath his crown to Alfred.

156
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:20,801
他那时候神志不清
He must have been delirious.

157
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:23,205
什么时候？
On which occasion?

158
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:29,166
我是国王的儿子
I am the son of the king.

159
00:11:30,520 --> 00:11:32,488
做好你的本职工作
Do your duty.

160
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:46,282
- 大人 - 啊，乌特雷德
- My lord. - Ah. Uhtred,

161
00:11:46,440 --> 00:11:51,367
请接受我的道歉，让你延缓释放，我有事缠身
please accept my apology for the delay in your release. I had matters to attend.

162
00:11:51,680 --> 00:11:53,489
要来点麦酒吗，神父？
Ale, Father?

163
00:11:53,640 --> 00:11:56,041
来一点，也给我们的客人倒上
A little, and for our guests.

164
00:11:56,200 --> 00:11:59,249
- 看来你说的是实话 - 我说的确实是实话
- (ALFRED) It seems you spoke the truth. - I did.

165
00:11:59,400 --> 00:12:02,688
虽然我清楚这次胜利只是暂时的
Though I realise our victory is temporary,

166
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:05,571
我欠你的情，威塞克斯也欠你的情
I am indebted, Wessex is indebted.

167
00:12:06,080 --> 00:12:08,242
- 我的道歉够吗？ - 不够，大人
- Is my apology enough? - It is not, lord.

168
00:12:09,640 --> 00:12:12,041
乌特雷德的意思是，道歉根本没有必要
What Uhtred means is that it is not necessary.

169
00:12:12,200 --> 00:12:14,680
我希望能像郡长一样被对待，因为我本来就是
I wish to be seen as an ealdorman, because I am.

170
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:17,605
- 那是在诺森布里亚，这里是威塞克斯 - 这里是英格兰
- In Northumbria. This is Wessex. - This is England.

171
00:12:17,760 --> 00:12:19,524
你说过要建立一个统一的王国
One kingdom is what you said.

172
00:12:19,680 --> 00:12:21,489
你现在什么土地都没有
You are without lands, completely.

173
00:12:21,640 --> 00:12:24,405
那正是我要的，也是我应得的——土地
Then that's what I want. That's what I deserve, land.

174
00:12:27,680 --> 00:12:30,251
我把你叫来只是想当面道谢
I brought you here solely to convey my thanks,

175
00:12:30,400 --> 00:12:32,482
但我们迟些还会再谈
but we shall talk further at some point,

176
00:12:32,640 --> 00:12:35,849
- 我还有事要处理 - 我给了你这场胜利，大人
- I have other matters to attend. - I gave you victory, lord,

177
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:38,287
- 还有什么比这更重要？ - 国王驾崩了
- what's more important? - (ALFRED) The king is dead.

178
00:12:40,120 --> 00:12:42,407
- 什么时候的事？ - 我刚刚离开他
- Since when? - (ALFRED) I have not long left him.

179
00:12:45,040 --> 00:12:49,090
我登基后的第一件事，就是向丹麦人提出和议
My first act as king will be to offer the Danes a peace.

180
00:12:49,240 --> 00:12:51,766
他们会觉得你软弱无能
(BRIDA) They will think you spineless,

181
00:12:52,560 --> 00:12:53,891
大人
Lord.

182
00:12:54,040 --> 00:12:56,441
那我就得让他们改变这个想法
Then I must convince them otherwise.

183
00:12:57,800 --> 00:13:01,600
姑娘，给我的寝室送些果子来，切好的苹果和牛奶
Girl, bring some fruits to my chamber, some chopped apples and milk.

184
00:13:01,760 --> 00:13:05,446
好好休息，洗个澡，吃顿好的，你们赢得了这一切
Rest, wash, eat well, you have earned it.

185
00:13:08,640 --> 00:13:12,770
你在说什么？跟未来的国王说话不能这副口气
What are you saying? You do not speak to a future king in that manner.

186
00:13:12,920 --> 00:13:14,888
他不是我的领主，也不会是我的国王
He's not my lord and won't be my king.

187
00:13:15,040 --> 00:13:17,964
听清楚了，乌特雷德，阿尔弗雷德才是值得追随的人
Hear me clearly, Uhtred. Alfred is the man to follow.

188
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:20,930
他是你回到贝班堡的路，你会以领主和主人的身份回去
He is your way back to Bebbanburg, as lord and master.

189
00:13:21,080 --> 00:13:23,845
乌特雷德走哪条路是他自己的事
Uhtred's path is Uhtred's business,

190
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:25,525
轮不到一个神父来指手画脚
not that of a priest.

191
00:13:26,720 --> 00:13:28,802
大人，请恕我失礼
Forgive me, lord,

192
00:13:29,040 --> 00:13:30,405
我得先离开
I must leave,

193
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:34,406
去祈祷，求主赐我力量，好驱散这些盘踞心头的邪念
pray for strength and to expunge these unholy thoughts that fill my mind.

194
00:13:41,520 --> 00:13:43,727
你想要威塞克斯的土地？
You want land in Wessex?

195
00:13:43,880 --> 00:13:46,406
那是我回贝班堡的路
It's my way back to Bebbanburg.

196
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:50,483
你在阿尔弗雷德那边挣到的任何财银，丹麦人都会抢走
Any silver you End under Alfred will be taken by the Danes,

197
00:13:51,080 --> 00:13:53,447
连你的命一起，他们根本打不过
along with your life. They can't be beaten.

198
00:13:55,480 --> 00:13:58,290
- 你为什么要这么做？ - 我说了，为了财富
- Why are you doing this? - I've said, wealth.

199
00:14:09,040 --> 00:14:10,485
大人，请借过
Excuse me, my lord,

200
00:14:10,640 --> 00:14:13,405
我正要去给阿尔弗雷德大人跑腿
I am on an errand to my Lord Alfred.

201
00:14:13,560 --> 00:14:16,882
- 这牛奶是给阿尔弗雷德的？ - 是的
- The milk is for Alfred? - It is.

202
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:24,531
不许说出去
Not a word.

203
00:14:25,920 --> 00:14:27,729
去吧
Go on.

204
00:14:32,560 --> 00:14:33,891


205
00:14:37,400 --> 00:14:39,528


206
00:14:40,480 --> 00:14:42,528
埃塞尔沃尔德公子
Master Aethelwold,

207
00:14:43,120 --> 00:14:45,771
你这个妄想称王的毛头小子
the man-child who would have himself be king.

208
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:50,087
出于对先王的敬重，阿尔弗雷德不希望动你
Out of respect for the late king, Alfred wishes no to harm to be done

209
00:14:50,240 --> 00:14:51,969
丑陋脑袋上的一根头发
to a hair of your ugly head,

210
00:14:52,120 --> 00:14:55,169
但他绝不会容忍你的无礼和谎言
but he will not put up with your insolence and lies.

211
00:14:55,320 --> 00:14:58,085
你自己的儿子也参与了我所谓的无礼
Your own son is party to my so called insolence.

212
00:14:58,240 --> 00:15:00,163
闭嘴
(ODDA) Quiet!

213
00:15:00,880 --> 00:15:03,360
不许把别人拖进你的阴谋
Don't you involve others in your Conspiracies.

214
00:15:04,920 --> 00:15:07,764
我的脑袋又不丑
My head is not ugly.

215
00:15:10,200 --> 00:15:12,965
你将被送往汉普顿的修道院
You're to be sent to Hampton, to a monastery,

216
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:15,282
接受教化，这是个漫长的过程
to be educated, it will be a long process.

217
00:15:15,440 --> 00:15:17,124
我是国王的儿子
I am the king's son.

218
00:15:17,280 --> 00:15:19,089
威塞克斯经不起内部分裂
(ODDA) Wessex cannot afford division.

219
00:15:19,880 --> 00:15:23,930
也经不起一个蠢孩子的胡言乱语，不管他出身贵贱
Nor can it afford the ramblings of an idiot child, noble or otherwise.

220
00:15:24,840 --> 00:15:26,683
去办吧
See to it.

221
00:15:27,360 --> 00:15:30,489
我能让他老实点吗？——我巴不得你这样
(LEOFRIC) May I make him docile? (ODDA) I wish you would.

222
00:15:30,640 --> 00:15:31,971
不，不，不！嗯！
(AETHELWOLD) No, no, no! Unh!

223
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:35,765


224
00:15:35,920 --> 00:15:37,445
进来
(ALFRED) Come.

225
00:15:39,120 --> 00:15:42,363
大人，您找我？
Lord, you wished to see me?

226
00:15:42,760 --> 00:15:45,047
是的，是的
I did, I did.

227
00:15:46,120 --> 00:15:50,250
你要去给古思伦，给丹麦人带个话
You will take a message to Guthrum, to the Danes.

228
00:15:50,440 --> 00:15:52,841
邀请他们在近日内前来谈判
You will invite them to negotiate within days,

229
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:54,525
时间地点由他们定
but at their own convenience.

230
00:15:56,360 --> 00:15:59,569
大人，若是要传话，宫里的人多的是
If it is a messenger you require, lord, there are plenty within the palace

231
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:02,724
我要的不是传话的人，是代我出面的人
It is not a messenger I require, it is a representative.

232
00:16:03,320 --> 00:16:04,970
你替我说话
You will speak for me.

233
00:16:05,120 --> 00:16:07,691
奥达，你代表我
Odda, you will speak as me.

234
00:16:08,720 --> 00:16:11,405
跟丹麦人什么都不能写在纸上
Nothing can be written for the Danes.

235
00:16:11,560 --> 00:16:13,289
我的书信已无意义,
My letters would be meaningless,

236
00:16:13,440 --> 00:16:15,442
所以这些话必须由我亲口说出,
therefore the words spoken

237
00:16:15,600 --> 00:16:17,921
必须是我的话,
must be my words,

238
00:16:18,080 --> 00:16:21,084
我将它们托付于你
and I entrust them to you.

239
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:25,091
那我很乐意做你的使者,大人
Then I shall gladly be your representative, lord.

240
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:27,885
谢谢你
Thank you.

241
00:16:34,080 --> 00:16:37,084
我盯着你看,冒犯你了吗?
Do I offend you? Watching you?

242
00:16:37,240 --> 00:16:40,084
没有,大人,从来没有
No, my lord, never.

243
00:16:41,880 --> 00:16:44,611
我会以命护你
I will defend you with my life.

244
00:16:46,480 --> 00:16:50,121
你是最珍贵的存在,你就是威塞克斯,就是英格兰,
You stand as everything that's precious. You are Wessex, England,

245
00:16:50,280 --> 00:16:53,648
永远值得珍视,永远不可侵犯,
always to be cherished, never to be violated,

246
00:16:53,800 --> 00:16:57,691
只能深情地爱护
only to be loved vigorously.

247
00:16:57,880 --> 00:16:59,211


248
00:16:59,360 --> 00:17:01,362
- 谁啊? - 是我,大人
- Who is it? - (BEOCCA) My lord.

249
00:17:01,520 --> 00:17:03,488
我的良心
My conscience.

250
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:09,522
大人,愿否与我一同为逝去的国王祈祷?
My lord, would you care to join me in prayer for the passing of the king?

251
00:17:09,680 --> 00:17:12,251
好,神父,多谢你
I will, Father. I give you my thanks.

252
00:17:13,600 --> 00:17:15,329
请见谅,大人,
Forgive me, my lord,

253
00:17:15,480 --> 00:17:17,642
牛奶变质了
the milk has soured.

254
00:17:22,560 --> 00:17:26,167
我受够奶和苹果了,我要吃肉
I am tired of milk and apples. I need meat.

255
00:17:26,320 --> 00:17:28,527
但大人，你是一个殉教者，不能吃肉
But you are a martyr, my lord, to meat.

256
00:17:28,680 --> 00:17:30,489
领主大人也需要吃饱
My lord needs feeding.

257
00:17:30,640 --> 00:17:32,802
领主大人不是圣人,也永远不会是
My lord is not a saint and never shall be.

258
00:17:32,960 --> 00:17:35,611
我从战场上幸存下来,我需要吃肉
I have survived battle, I need meat.

259
00:17:37,880 --> 00:17:41,362
我们一起祈祷吧,大人,祈求力量
We shall pray together, my lord, for strength.

260
00:17:41,960 --> 00:17:44,531
为什么这也算是罪?
Why does it have to be a sin?

261
00:17:52,560 --> 00:17:55,086
这已经是个重担了
Already, it is a burden.

262
00:17:56,960 --> 00:17:59,611
好像从来都不是我想做什么
It seems never to be about what I would wish to do,

263
00:17:59,760 --> 00:18:02,889
而是我必须做什么
it is about what I must do.

264
00:18:06,840 --> 00:18:11,289
求天主赐我力量, 让我能像你一样戴好这顶王冠
Ask God to give me the strength to wear the crown as well as you.

265
00:18:20,440 --> 00:18:22,329
贝奥卡神父
Father Beocca.

266
00:18:22,480 --> 00:18:24,448
- 稍等- 是, 大人
- A moment. - Yes, lord.

267
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:27,046
乌特雷德或许还有用处
Uhtred may well have a use.

268
00:18:27,280 --> 00:18:29,886
我很高兴您能这么想 大人
I'm pleased that is what you think, lord.

269
00:18:30,040 --> 00:18:32,008
这个布丽达, 她跟他是什么关系?
This Brida, she is what to him?

270
00:18:32,160 --> 00:18:34,003
- 我说是个累赘- 妻子?
- I would say a hindrance. - A wife?

271
00:18:34,160 --> 00:18:37,403
- 不不, 绝对不是- 她坐立不安
- No, no. Never, no. - She is restless.

272
00:18:37,560 --> 00:18:41,645
- 她是他肩上的恶魔, 我担心- 但他很在乎她
- She is the devil on his shoulder, I fear. - But he is fond of her.

273
00:18:42,240 --> 00:18:45,050
是啊, 他就是这种人
Yes, that is his way.

274
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:46,890
走着瞧吧
We shall see.

275
00:18:47,040 --> 00:18:49,486
- 谢谢- 大人
- Thank you. - My lord.

276
00:19:21,240 --> 00:19:22,969
我带来一封信
(YOUNGER) I carry a message.

277
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:26,090
- 来自阿尔弗雷德国王- 阿尔弗雷德国王是谁?
- From King Alfred. - Who is King Alfred?

278
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:28,242
他是威塞克斯国王阿尔弗雷德
He is, Alfred, King of Wessex.

279
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:31,563
他邀请古思伦伯爵前来谈和
He invites the Earl Guthrum to negotiate a peace.

280
00:19:31,720 --> 00:19:33,609
你就是古思伦?
You are Guthrum?

281
00:19:33,840 --> 00:19:36,320
从马上下来, 小子
Get down from your horse, boy.

282
00:19:36,480 --> 00:19:39,370
从马上下来, 好好看看我
Get down from your horse and look at me.

283
00:19:45,280 --> 00:19:48,045
你长得不错嘛
You are a beauty.

284
00:19:50,120 --> 00:19:52,726
告诉那个国王, 他叫什么来着?
Tell this king, what was his name?

285
00:19:52,880 --> 00:19:54,689
阿尔弗雷德
Alfred.

286
00:19:55,520 --> 00:19:58,808
告诉阿尔弗雷德国王, 古思伦接受他的邀请,
Tell King Alfred that Guthrum accepts his invitation,

287
00:19:58,960 --> 00:20:02,203
我会在路上等候, 亲自出迎
and I will watch for him and I shall ride out and meet him.

288
00:20:02,360 --> 00:20:04,567
我会转达您的话, 大人
I will pass on your message, lord.

289
00:20:09,200 --> 00:20:11,009
这匹马现在是我的了
This horse belongs to me now.

290
00:20:14,440 --> 00:20:17,649
乌特雷德, 阿尔弗雷德很想重用你
Uhtred, Alfred is keen to find a use for you,

291
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:21,566
但布丽达……她只会添乱
but Brida is... She's not a help.

292
00:20:21,720 --> 00:20:23,290
你能不能让她离他远一点
Perhaps you could just keep her away from him.

293
00:20:23,440 --> 00:20:26,125
阿尔弗雷德知道我能派上用场, 我已经证明过了
Alfred knows I can be of use, and I have proven it.

294
00:20:26,280 --> 00:20:28,601
现在轮到他证明他对我有用了
Now he must prove he can be of use to me.

295
00:20:28,760 --> 00:20:31,081
- 他将会成为国王 - 你可以效忠于他
- He will be king. - And you can serve him.

296
00:20:31,240 --> 00:20:32,924
我来这里是为了我自己
I'm here to serve myself.

297
00:20:33,080 --> 00:20:36,323
阿尔弗雷德对我来说不过是一条路，让我夺回失去的一切
Alfred means nothing but a path to take back what is mine.

298
00:20:36,480 --> 00:20:39,370
我的土地, 我的财富, 还有我的封号
My land, my wealth, and my title.

299
00:20:39,520 --> 00:20:42,490
他能用上我, 但我也能用上他
He will have a use for me, but I will have a use for him.

300
00:20:42,960 --> 00:20:46,009
别小看他, 他会把你看穿的
Do not think him naive. He will see right through you.

301
00:20:46,160 --> 00:20:49,323
他只会看到我想让他看到的东西
He will see what I allow him to see.

302
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:54,250
听着, 乌特雷德, 你现在是个战士, 不是谋士
Look, Uhtred, right now you are a warrior, not a thinker.

303
00:20:55,120 --> 00:20:57,122
不过假以时日, 这一点也会来的
Though, in time, this will come.

304
00:20:58,120 --> 00:21:00,646
你很像你父亲, 而他两者兼备
You are much like your father, and he was both.

305
00:21:00,800 --> 00:21:03,531
你现在是阿尔弗雷德的神父了, 贝奥卡
You are AIfred's priest now, Beocca.

306
00:21:12,760 --> 00:21:14,922
想找人作伴吗, 姑娘?
(LEOFRIC) You looking for company, girl?

307
00:21:15,240 --> 00:21:19,086
我宁可与众神为伴, 也不愿跟蠢货待在一起
I prefer the company of the gods to stupid men.

308
00:21:19,680 --> 00:21:21,808
那改天吧?
Another time, then?

309
00:22:49,040 --> 00:22:50,883


310
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:56,209
- 早安, 乌特雷德 - 早安, 大人
- Good morning, Uhtred. - (UHTRED) Good morning, lord.

311
00:23:05,120 --> 00:23:07,088
- 好一件锁子甲 - 是的
- That's a fine coat of mail. - (ALFRED) It is.

312
00:23:07,240 --> 00:23:11,245
这是你的了, 一套撒克逊武士的战甲, 送给你的
And it is yours, the battle dress of a Saxon warrior. A gift.

313
00:23:11,400 --> 00:23:14,006
换什么? 凡事都有代价
(UHTRED) In return for what? There's always a price.

314
00:23:14,160 --> 00:23:15,650
你已经付清了
(ALFRED) Which you have paid in full.

315
00:23:15,800 --> 00:23:17,768
那场山岗上的胜仗
Our victory at the hill.

316
00:23:17,920 --> 00:23:22,005
小奥达, 你向乌特雷德道歉了吗?
Young Odda, have you offered your apologies to Uhtred?

317
00:23:24,280 --> 00:23:27,489
我真心道歉, 你说的是实话
My sincere apologies, you spoke the truth.

318
00:23:28,920 --> 00:23:31,287
稍微鞠个躬, 也许?
A small bow, perhaps?

319
00:23:37,160 --> 00:23:38,764
你可以退下了
You may leave us now.

320
00:23:45,040 --> 00:23:49,170
一个好国王要善于听取良言, 乌特雷德
A good king relies upon good advice, Uhtred.

321
00:23:49,800 --> 00:23:52,963
比如我的侄子埃塞尔沃尔德, 先王之子,
For example, my nephew, Aethelwold, the king's son,

322
00:23:53,120 --> 00:23:55,726
他年纪轻轻却自认是理所当然的王位继承人
he is young but sees himself as the rightful heir.

323
00:23:55,880 --> 00:23:58,247
我该怎么处置他?
How am I to deal with him?

324
00:24:01,280 --> 00:24:03,123
您应该杀了他, 大人,
You should kill him, lord,

325
00:24:03,280 --> 00:24:05,601
就像我叔父埃尔弗里克想杀我一样
as my own uncle, Aelfric, would kill me.

326
00:24:06,240 --> 00:24:08,368
- 不杀他就是示弱 - 你太放肆了
- Not to kill him shows weakness. - You are being insolent.

327
00:24:08,520 --> 00:24:09,851
我允许他这样说,
I will allow it,

328
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:12,526
这是他骨子里的异教徒在说话
it is the pagan in him speaking.

329
00:24:12,680 --> 00:24:14,489
你的思维方式像个丹麦人, 乌特雷德
You think like a Dane, Uhtred.

330
00:24:15,280 --> 00:24:19,205
我若杀了埃塞尔沃尔德, 就等于承认他对王位有正当的主张,
If I kill Aethelwold, I am admitting he has legitimate claim to the throne,

331
00:24:19,360 --> 00:24:21,761
而他并没有, 这才是我的想法
which he does not. That is how I think.

332
00:24:23,000 --> 00:24:27,130
不过, 在议会里留一个异教徒的头脑倒是有用
But to have a specimen of the heathen mind in council will be useful.

333
00:24:27,960 --> 00:24:31,362
丹麦人最怕什么?
What do they fear most, the Danes?

334
00:24:31,800 --> 00:24:33,484
他们是战士, 生来就为战斗
They're warriors, live to fight.

335
00:24:33,640 --> 00:24:36,371
但要是打了败仗, 就像那场山岗之战, 然后呢?
But when they lose, as at the hill, what then?

336
00:24:36,520 --> 00:24:39,444
打仗时, 他们宁可撤退也不愿损兵折将
In battle, they'd rather retreat than lose too many men.

337
00:24:39,600 --> 00:24:42,171
如果他们有什么畏惧的,那就是折损人马
If they fear anything at all, it is losing men.

338
00:24:42,320 --> 00:24:44,766
他们嗜战,却不甘认败,
They love to fight but hate to lose,

339
00:24:44,920 --> 00:24:46,490
这倒不算什么新鲜事
hardly a revelation.

340
00:24:46,880 --> 00:24:48,644
奥达似乎不把你的意见放在眼里
Odda appears not to value your council.

341
00:24:48,800 --> 00:24:50,131
- 确实不放- 我也无所谓
- (ODDA) I do not. - I care not.

342
00:24:50,280 --> 00:24:53,966
你请求被认定为郡长一事,我一直在考虑
I have been thinking on your request to be recognised as an ealdorman.

343
00:24:54,120 --> 00:24:56,566
- 简直是无稽之谈- 我本就是郡长
- (ODDA) Which is a nonsense. - I am an ealdorman.

344
00:24:56,720 --> 00:24:59,963
你名下连一只羊都没有,更别提放牧的土地了
Without a goat to your name, never mind the land to graze it.

345
00:25:00,120 --> 00:25:02,202
- 我是郡长- 你可否考虑
- I'm an ealdorman. - Would you consider

346
00:25:02,360 --> 00:25:04,169
以联姻的方式成为郡长?
becoming an ealdorman by marriage?

347
00:25:04,320 --> 00:25:07,290
我知道有门亲事,能给你带来土地和头衔
I know of a marriage that would bring you land and title.

348
00:25:07,440 --> 00:25:10,728
- 我不需要妻子，大人     - 妻子能对你有帮助  - 变老？
- I have no need of a wife,lord - A woman helps you grow.  -Grow old？

349
00:25:10,880 --> 00:25:13,804
扎下根来,这正是你所欠缺的
Grow roots, and that is what you are missing.

350
00:25:13,960 --> 00:25:17,123
婚姻能证明你对威塞克斯的忠心
Marriage would show your commitment, to Wessex.

351
00:25:17,280 --> 00:25:19,408
我已经证明过了
I have shown commitment.

352
00:25:19,560 --> 00:25:21,801
您自己也说过,是我给了您这场在山岭的胜利
You've said yourself, I gave you victory at the hill.

353
00:25:21,960 --> 00:25:25,009
你出了力,但这场胜利是威塞克斯的战士打下来的
You helped, but the victory was won by the men of Wessex.

354
00:25:25,160 --> 00:25:27,891
而你如今却拒绝通过这门婚事融入他们
Whom you now refuse to join through this marriage.

355
00:25:28,040 --> 00:25:31,522
土地和银子是每个男人都想要的,我也不例外
Land and silver is what all men desire and I'm no different.

356
00:25:31,680 --> 00:25:33,444
但请相信我,大人,我不需要妻子
But believe me, lord, I have no need of a wife.

357
00:25:35,240 --> 00:25:38,050
- 我的剑为您效命   - 但有条件
- My sword is yours. - (ODDA) At a price?

358
00:25:39,240 --> 00:25:42,642
我所拥有的一切都被人夺走了
Everything that I have has been taken from me.

359
00:25:43,280 --> 00:25:45,521
我需要头衔,需要积攒自己的财富
I need title, I need to make my wealth.

360
00:25:45,680 --> 00:25:49,287
你是打算为我效忠，还是只是当一个雇佣兵?
Are you are offering me your sword or are you selling me your sword?

361
00:25:50,760 --> 00:25:53,081
要成为郡长,你必须拥有土地,
To become an ealdorman you must possess land,

362
00:25:53,240 --> 00:25:57,564
这是法令       但如果在接下来的谈判中
that is the law. However, stand at my side

363
00:25:57,720 --> 00:26:01,930
你站在我这边, 帮我看透对手
during the negotiations ahead, help me read my enemy

364
00:26:02,080 --> 00:26:03,764
作为回报
and in return

365
00:26:03,920 --> 00:26:07,845
我们再好好谈谈赏赐的事
we shall talk further of wealth and reward.

366
00:26:22,440 --> 00:26:23,771


367
00:26:23,960 --> 00:26:25,962


368
00:26:26,840 --> 00:26:29,320


369
00:26:30,360 --> 00:26:32,647
那么, 你看到什么了?
Well, what did you see?

370
00:26:32,920 --> 00:26:36,083
- 他们让你看到了什么? - 我看到的是我自己的事
- What did they show you? - What I saw is my business.

371
00:26:36,240 --> 00:26:38,561
我感觉不舒服
I feel unwell.

372
00:26:44,000 --> 00:26:45,411
来
Here.

373
00:26:46,880 --> 00:26:48,484
水
Water.

374
00:27:04,800 --> 00:27:07,485
我们身处此地是命运的安排
Where we find ourselves is fate,

375
00:27:08,320 --> 00:27:10,448
是那三位纺者的旨意
the work of the three spinners,

376
00:27:10,600 --> 00:27:14,844
她们深藏在我们脚下的大地里, 是她们把我们带到了这里
they sit deep in this earth beneath us and they have brought us here.

377
00:27:16,120 --> 00:27:17,963
我们该走了...
We should go...

378
00:27:19,320 --> 00:27:21,163
去康沃卢姆
To Cornwalum,

379
00:27:21,320 --> 00:27:23,687
威尔士, 爱尔兰
Wales, Ireland,

380
00:27:23,840 --> 00:27:25,444
- 去哪儿都行 - 为什么?
- anywhere. - Why?

381
00:27:26,000 --> 00:27:27,604
逃离这里
Escape.

382
00:27:31,360 --> 00:27:33,249
为了安全
Safety.

383
00:27:35,640 --> 00:27:37,927
我看见了拉格纳的船
I saw Ragnar's ship.

384
00:27:38,080 --> 00:27:41,004
- 往事号吗? - 不, 是风蛇号
- The past? - No. Wind Viper.

385
00:27:42,280 --> 00:27:43,611
是小拉格纳?
Young Ragnar?

386
00:27:43,760 --> 00:27:47,048
我就在那船上, 我亲眼看见的
I was there on the ship. I saw it.

387
00:27:47,600 --> 00:27:49,807
我想离开这里
I want to leave here.

388
00:27:50,040 --> 00:27:51,849
跟我来
Come with me.

389
00:27:54,520 --> 00:27:56,090
跟我来
Come with me.

390
00:27:56,240 --> 00:27:58,891
我已经向阿尔弗雷德许下承诺
I've given a promise to Alfred.

391
00:27:59,840 --> 00:28:02,127
出席谈判, 出谋划策
To attend the negotiations, to advise.

392
00:28:08,120 --> 00:28:10,851
布丽达, 我们无处可去
Bride, there's no place else for us to go.

393
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:13,685
我们不能留在这里
We cannot stay here.

394
00:28:15,520 --> 00:28:17,409
这是个开始
It's a beginning.

395
00:28:20,840 --> 00:28:22,524
你走吧
Leave me.

396
00:28:24,320 --> 00:28:26,846
我们不能就这样在各处流荡, 什么都不做
We cannot wander the country and do nothing.

397
00:28:27,000 --> 00:28:28,843
你怎么能信任他?
How can you trust him?

398
00:28:29,000 --> 00:28:31,082
你怎么知道他不会把你直接交给古思伦
How do you know he won't simply turn you over to Guthrum

399
00:28:31,240 --> 00:28:33,686
再转交给乌巴? 你对他一无所知
to pass on to Ubba? You know nothing about him.

400
00:28:33,840 --> 00:28:36,320
我信任贝奥卡神父, 而贝奥卡是他的神父
I trust Father Beocca, and Beocca is his priest.

401
00:28:36,480 --> 00:28:38,403
我说了, 走开
I said leave me.

402
00:28:44,880 --> 00:28:47,611
你没有和我一起在那条船上!
You were not on the ship with me!

403
00:28:48,360 --> 00:28:51,364
去找阿尔弗雷德吧, 我倒要亲眼看他怎么出卖你!
Go to Alfred, and I will watch him betray you!

404
00:29:10,480 --> 00:29:13,450
那么, 我们对这个阿尔弗雷德了解多少?
So, what do we know of this Alfred?

405
00:29:13,600 --> 00:29:15,887
他体弱多病, 软弱无能
That he is sickly, he's weak.

406
00:29:16,040 --> 00:29:18,247
他想要谈判
He wants to negotiate.

407
00:29:18,720 --> 00:29:21,200
看来他根本不是个战士
Turns out that he's no warrior.

408
00:29:21,920 --> 00:29:24,844
- 但他打败了你, 古思伦 - 哈哈哈
- But he beat you, Guthrum. - (GUTHRUM) Heh, heh, heh.

409
00:29:29,920 --> 00:29:32,605
那上面写的什么?
So, what does it say?

410
00:29:45,680 --> 00:29:47,808
谈判
Negotiation.

411
00:29:49,160 --> 00:29:50,889
白银
Silver.

412
00:29:51,360 --> 00:29:54,011
我们会拿走他的白银
We will take his silver

413
00:29:55,240 --> 00:29:56,924
还有他的土地
and his land.

414
00:29:57,080 --> 00:30:00,004
他若拒绝呢?他绝不会拒绝的
(GUTHRUM) And If he refuses? (UBBA) He will never refuse.

415
00:30:00,160 --> 00:30:04,609
他想活命, 也想被称为国王, 哈哈哈
He wants to live and he wants to be called king. Heh, heh, heh.

416
00:31:31,640 --> 00:31:33,642
天主在天之灵,
Our God in his heaven,

417
00:31:33,800 --> 00:31:39,682
求你垂顾你忠心的仆人阿尔弗雷德
we ask you to find favour with your devoted servant, Alfred.

418
00:31:40,320 --> 00:31:43,529
赐他勇气、力量与智慧
Bless him with courage, strength and wisdom.

419
00:31:43,680 --> 00:31:46,081
永不离他左右, 阿门
Never leave his side. Amen.

420
00:31:46,240 --> 00:31:47,890
阿门
(ALL) Amen.

421
00:31:48,040 --> 00:31:52,523
赐他纯洁神圣的心念,
(SELBIX) Allow him pure and holy thoughts,

422
00:31:52,680 --> 00:31:56,810
赐他能力, 以吾王之身在世间完成你的旨意
and the power to carry out your work on this earth as our king.

423
00:31:58,200 --> 00:32:02,524
愿这涂油礼成就你的意志, 降福于阿尔弗雷德
Allow this anointing of Alfred to enable your will.

424
00:32:03,160 --> 00:32:05,970
你是天主选立的国王, 威塞克斯的阿尔弗雷德
You are God's king, Alfred of Wessex.

425
00:32:07,360 --> 00:32:09,886
阿尔佛雷德国王万岁
Vivat Rex alfredus!

426
00:32:10,440 --> 00:32:12,966
阿尔佛雷德国王万岁
Vivat Rex alfredus!

427
00:32:14,320 --> 00:32:16,687
阿尔佛雷德国王万岁
Vivat Rex alfredus!

428
00:32:17,120 --> 00:32:19,646
阿尔佛雷德国王万岁
Vivat Rex alfredus!

429
00:32:21,280 --> 00:32:23,009
阿尔佛雷德国王万岁
Vivat Rex alfredus!

430
00:32:26,800 --> 00:32:29,451
阿尔佛雷德国王万岁
Vivat Rex alfredus!

431
00:32:42,800 --> 00:32:45,121
阿尔佛雷德国王万岁
Vivat Rex alfredus!

432
00:32:47,840 --> 00:32:50,844
没有你的日子, 我难以想象
I can't imagine a time without you.

433
00:32:52,360 --> 00:32:54,886
阿尔佛雷德国王万岁
Vivat Rex alfredus! 

434
00:33:20,880 --> 00:33:22,803
那是古思伦?
It is Guthrum?

435
00:33:23,040 --> 00:33:24,405
是
Yes.

436
00:33:24,560 --> 00:33:27,848
你看他头发里夹着一根骨头
You can see a bone in his hair.

437
00:33:28,000 --> 00:33:30,002
那是他母亲的肋骨
It's his mother's rib.

438
00:33:30,640 --> 00:33:32,483
真叫人动容
How endearing.

439
00:33:32,880 --> 00:33:34,245
其他人呢?
And the others?

440
00:33:34,400 --> 00:33:37,131
那是乌巴, 那个大块头
(UHTRED) It is Ubba. The big man.

441
00:33:37,280 --> 00:33:38,964
首领乌巴也来了?
The Chieftain, Ubba, is with them?

442
00:33:39,120 --> 00:33:40,770
你说他在北边
You said he was in the north.

443
00:33:41,480 --> 00:33:43,448
他现在在这儿
(ALFRED) Now he is here.

444
00:33:45,320 --> 00:33:47,163
这倒是好事
This is good.

445
00:34:06,960 --> 00:34:08,291
所以你就是阿尔弗雷德,
(GUTHRUM) So you are Alfred,

446
00:34:08,440 --> 00:34:11,046
- 威塞克斯的国王? - 正是
-the king of Wessex? - (ALFRED) I am.

447
00:34:11,200 --> 00:34:14,249
- 你是古思伦伯爵? - 是的
- You are Earl Guthrum? - Yes.

448
00:34:14,400 --> 00:34:16,687
若想要和平, 你得付出代价
If you want peace, you'll have to pay.

449
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:19,604
你就是乌巴伯爵
And you are the Earl Ubba.

450
00:34:19,760 --> 00:34:22,411
- 欢迎 - 说吧
- Welcome. - Speak.

451
00:34:22,680 --> 00:34:26,048
以商定数量的粮食、牲畜和银两为交换,
In exchange for an agreed amount of grain, livestock and silver,

452
00:34:26,200 --> 00:34:29,807
我提议你们率船队返回伦敦, 并留守于此
I propose that you and your ships return to Lundene and remain there.

453
00:34:29,960 --> 00:34:33,123
我还提议你们将活动范围限于东盎格利亚,
I further propose you confine yourselves to East Anglia,

454
00:34:33,280 --> 00:34:34,964
麦西亚和诺森布里亚
Mercia and Northumbria.

455
00:34:35,120 --> 00:34:39,330
威塞克斯是撒克逊人的土地, 因此对所有丹麦人禁止踏入
Wessex is Saxon, and as such out-of-bounds to all Danes.

456
00:34:39,480 --> 00:34:41,642
我们不会离开威塞克斯的
We'll not be leaving Wessex.

457
00:34:41,800 --> 00:34:43,245
我们才刚到
We only just arrived.

458
00:34:43,400 --> 00:34:45,004
那你们就等着挨饿吧
Then you will starve.

459
00:34:46,040 --> 00:34:47,769
你们粮食匮乏,
You have little food,

460
00:34:48,760 --> 00:34:50,444
没有栖身之所, 军队也已大伤元气
no shelter and a weakened army.

461
00:34:50,600 --> 00:34:53,570
若你觉得我们已是强弩之末, 为何还要求和?
If you believe us weakened, why seek peace?

462
00:34:54,360 --> 00:34:56,761
这是我身为基督徒的本性
It is the Christian in me.

463
00:34:57,000 --> 00:34:58,445
是我主的旨意
The will of my God.

464
00:34:58,600 --> 00:35:02,161
- 哼, 我不想听什么神的说辞 - 是天主, 只有唯一的天主
- Oh, I will hear no talk of gods. - God. There is only one.

465
00:35:02,320 --> 00:35:03,890
你该谈的是粮食,
You will talk of grain,

466
00:35:04,560 --> 00:35:08,485
- 马匹、银两和土地 - 土地的事, 免谈
- horses, silver and land. - I will not talk of land.

467
00:35:09,400 --> 00:35:11,209
他们在写什么?
What do they write?

468
00:35:11,360 --> 00:35:12,771
他们在记录我们说的话
(ALFRED) They write what we speak.

469
00:35:12,920 --> 00:35:15,002
- 每一个字? - 是的, 每一个字
- Every word? - Yes, every word.

470
00:35:15,160 --> 00:35:18,004
那我要是说屁股 
Then may I say arse,

471
00:35:18,160 --> 00:35:19,889
乳房、做爱和狗屎呢
tits, hump and turd.

472
00:35:20,440 --> 00:35:23,046
他们记录历史，我们在这里创造历史
They record history. We are here creating history.

473
00:35:23,200 --> 00:35:25,646
后人会读到这场会面
People will read of this very meeting.

474
00:35:25,800 --> 00:35:27,723
我在等你们投降
I'm waiting to hear your surrender.

475
00:35:27,880 --> 00:35:30,167
你们退回伦敦，我们会给你们报酬
You will be paid for your return to Lundene.

476
00:35:30,320 --> 00:35:33,847
其他就没什么好谈的，我们不会投降
There are no more terms and there will be no surrender.

477
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:38,562
古思伦不会离开雷丁厄姆
Guthrum here will not leave Readingum.

478
00:35:38,720 --> 00:35:40,484
那我就再说一遍，他会饿死的
Then I say again, he will starve.

479
00:35:40,640 --> 00:35:42,130
我们会突袭
(GUTHRUM) we win raid.

480
00:35:42,280 --> 00:35:43,611
我们会杀人
We will kill.

481
00:35:43,760 --> 00:35:45,808
那你们还会再折损人马
And you will lose yet more men.

482
00:35:46,040 --> 00:35:48,771
这是你想要的吗，古思伦伯爵,
Is that your wish, Earl Guthrum,

483
00:35:48,920 --> 00:35:50,365
折损兵力?
to lose men?

484
00:35:50,520 --> 00:35:54,525
你剩下的勇士们或许会去另寻新主
Your surviving warriors may look to find a new lord.

485
00:35:54,680 --> 00:35:56,603
你召集这次会面就是来羞辱我的?
Did you call a meeting to insult me?

486
00:35:56,760 --> 00:35:59,001
我带来的是和平和事实
I offer peace and I offer facts.

487
00:36:01,000 --> 00:36:03,571
拿他的人头来，你就能得到和平
(UBBA) His head, and you can have your peace.

488
00:36:04,640 --> 00:36:06,244
就是他
Him.

489
00:36:13,040 --> 00:36:16,010
乌特雷德 拉格纳松
Uhtred Ragnarson.

490
00:36:16,960 --> 00:36:18,325
叛徒
A traitor.

491
00:36:25,280 --> 00:36:29,205
- 无话可说? - 我只会跟小拉格纳谈
- Nothing to say? - I'll speak to young Ragnar.

492
00:36:29,360 --> 00:36:32,284
其他的丹麦人不值得我的敬重
No other Dane has my respect.

493
00:36:32,440 --> 00:36:34,488
用他的人头换和平
His head, for peace.

494
00:36:34,640 --> 00:36:36,290
你要乌特雷德的人头来换和平?
You want Uhtred here for peace?

495
00:36:36,440 --> 00:36:39,967
不要金银，不要粮草，不要马匹?
No silver, no grain, no horses?

496
00:36:40,120 --> 00:36:43,090
我们要白银,还要叛徒的脑袋
We want silver, and the traitors head.

497
00:36:43,240 --> 00:36:46,642
这就是条件还有你,阿尔弗雷德,哈,
These are the terms. And you, Alfred, heh,

498
00:36:46,800 --> 00:36:49,201
你可以继续当国王,
you may remain king,

499
00:36:49,360 --> 00:36:53,490
但我们要占领所有撒克逊人的要塞
but we will occupy all of the Saxon forts.

500
00:36:53,640 --> 00:36:57,167
你们想占要塞,就去占,拿去
If you wish to occupy the fortresses, then do it, take them.

501
00:36:59,800 --> 00:37:01,484
你们到目前为止拿下过几座?
How many have you taken to date?

502
00:37:02,400 --> 00:37:05,688
- 他们到目前为止拿下过几座? - 一座都没有,大人
- How many have they taken to date? - None, lord.

503
00:37:08,800 --> 00:37:11,007
我们随时可以拿下所有要塞!
We can take all fortresses at any time!

504
00:37:11,880 --> 00:37:15,407
整个英格兰都是我们打下来的
We have taken the whole of England.

505
00:37:17,840 --> 00:37:20,207
威塞克斯也一样
And we can do the same with Wessex.

506
00:37:20,360 --> 00:37:22,647
我把话说清楚
Let me be clear.

507
00:37:22,800 --> 00:37:25,644
我已经准备好重新开战，我们人比你们多
I'm prepared to return to the sword. We outnumber you.

508
00:37:25,800 --> 00:37:29,885
我们人多势众,战力凶悍,但我更愿意谈和
We are many and we are dangerous, but I would prefer to establish a peace.

509
00:37:30,040 --> 00:37:32,008
乌特雷德也会保住他的人头
And Uhtred here shall keep his head,

510
00:37:32,160 --> 00:37:35,687
但我会给你们一大笔钱,换你们离开威塞克斯
but I will pay you well to leave Wessex.

511
00:37:36,480 --> 00:37:38,847
这就是后人会读到的
That is what people will read.

512
00:37:39,000 --> 00:37:41,241
阿尔弗雷德寻求和平
That Alfred sought peace.

513
00:37:41,400 --> 00:37:46,486
阿尔弗雷德向乌巴大人和古思伦大人献上白银,以换取和平
Alfred paid Lords Ubba and Guthrum in silver in exchange for peace.

514
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:50,288
是我主动要结束这场仗的
It is I who is seeking an end to the fighting.

515
00:37:51,160 --> 00:37:53,640
就这样写下去
That is what will be written.

516
00:38:15,600 --> 00:38:17,045
乌特雷德
Uhtred.

517
00:38:21,400 --> 00:38:25,041
我绝不会把你交给乌巴
I would never have given you up to Ubba.

518
00:38:25,200 --> 00:38:27,362
但你确实有过这个想法,大人
But the thought did cross your mind, lord.

519
00:38:27,520 --> 00:38:29,329
从来没有
Not once.

520
00:38:29,480 --> 00:38:30,811
事实是,
The fact is,

521
00:38:30,960 --> 00:38:33,850
我希望你宣誓效忠,
I would like you to swear an oath,

522
00:38:34,000 --> 00:38:37,402
以圣物为证, 效力一年
on holy relics, a years' service.

523
00:38:37,800 --> 00:38:40,644
期间你要帮助我的战士明白
During which time you will help my warriors understand

524
00:38:40,800 --> 00:38:44,407
那些异教徒不过也是血肉之躯,
that the heathens are but men,

525
00:38:44,560 --> 00:38:46,528
作为回报, 假以时日,
and in return, and in time,

526
00:38:46,680 --> 00:38:49,160
你会得到应有的报酬
you shall have your own reward.

527
00:38:49,400 --> 00:38:51,801
贝班堡的乌特雷德
Uhtred of Bebbanburg.

528
00:38:54,600 --> 00:38:56,204
一年
One year.

529
00:39:33,800 --> 00:39:35,325
孩子
(MAN) Boy.

530
00:39:44,040 --> 00:39:45,724
给国王带去
For the king.

531
00:39:57,320 --> 00:40:00,290
他们被拦住了, 但也仅此而已
(ALFRED) They have been halted, but nothing more.

532
00:40:01,000 --> 00:40:03,241
他们还没有被打败
They are not defeated.

533
00:40:03,760 --> 00:40:06,366
我们眼下的任务, 说简单简单, 说难也难
Our task now is both simple and impossible.

534
00:40:06,520 --> 00:40:10,241
- 我们得摸清他们的动向 - 丹麦人的做法就一个字, 打
- We determine what they will do. - They will do what Danes do, attack.

535
00:40:10,400 --> 00:40:11,845
怎么打? 在哪打? 何时打? 来多少人?
(ALFRED) How? Where? When? How many?

536
00:40:12,000 --> 00:40:15,721
我们本该庆祝和平的, 非得谈打仗吗?
We're supposed to be Celebrating peace, do we have to talk of fighting?

537
00:40:15,880 --> 00:40:19,043
必须谈, 亲爱的, 因为这份和平撑不久
(ALFRED) We do, my dear, because the peace will not last.

538
00:40:19,480 --> 00:40:23,201
他们至少还需要一年才能集结起第二支大军
It'll take at least a year before they can gather a second great army.

539
00:40:23,360 --> 00:40:25,124
- 你能保证吗? - 儿子
(YOUNGER) Do we have your word? (ODDA) Son.

540
00:40:25,280 --> 00:40:26,691
这儿有肉吃吗?
Is there any meat here?

541
00:40:26,840 --> 00:40:29,286
- 她该来这里吗? - 布丽达是我的客人
- Should she even be here? - Bride is my guest.

542
00:40:29,440 --> 00:40:32,649
你早该接受国王给你赐婚的好意
You should have taken up the king's offer of a wife.

543
00:40:32,800 --> 00:40:34,131
一位贵女
A lady.

544
00:40:34,280 --> 00:40:37,284
接下来会发生的事, 就是他们从陆路和海上同时来犯
(ALFRED) What happens next is that they will come by land and sea.

545
00:40:37,440 --> 00:40:40,330
他们会把我们的军队分割成两路, 甚至更多
They will split our army in two, possibly more.

546
00:40:40,480 --> 00:40:44,326
乌特雷德说的也许没错，这事可能一年内不会发生，甚至更久
Now, Uhtred may be correct, this may not occur for a year or more,

547
00:40:44,480 --> 00:40:48,326
但有一点是清楚的——我们需要船
but what is clear is that we need ships.

548
00:40:48,920 --> 00:40:52,049
四面环水，我们的船却少得可怜
We are bordered by water, yet we have so few ships.

549
00:40:52,200 --> 00:40:53,929
别指望我上船
You'll not get me on a ship.

550
00:40:54,080 --> 00:40:55,844
我可以让我儿子去
I'll volunteer my son.

551
00:40:56,000 --> 00:40:59,322
要守住我们的海岸，就得把目光放到海岸之外
To save our shores, we have to look beyond them,

552
00:40:59,480 --> 00:41:01,642
而且为了侍奉天主
and to serve God,

553
00:41:01,800 --> 00:41:05,043
- 祂的圣言必须远播 - 阿门，颂主荣耀
- his word must travel. - Amen. Praise him.

554
00:41:05,200 --> 00:41:06,611
乌特雷德，丹麦人船头的那些怪兽
Uhtred, the beasts,

555
00:41:07,240 --> 00:41:08,765
on the prows of Danes' ships,

556
00:41:08,920 --> 00:41:12,003
是他们神明的象征吗
they are a representation of their gods?

557
00:41:12,160 --> 00:41:14,162
不，大人，不过就是兽头装饰
No, lord. They are just beasts.

558
00:41:14,320 --> 00:41:18,086
靠近陆地时可以卸下来，免得惊扰到土地上的神灵
They can be lifted, so not to frighten the spirits of the land.

559
00:41:18,240 --> 00:41:20,083
土地的神灵，哈哈
Spirits of the land. Heh, heh.

560
00:41:20,240 --> 00:41:23,847
我倒想知道，他们为什么有人要把自己的牙磨尖
I'd like to know why some of them make their own teeth into points.

561
00:41:24,000 --> 00:41:26,128
- 真有这回事？ - 有些人会这样，夫人
- They do that? - Some, lady.

562
00:41:26,280 --> 00:41:28,009
愿主保佑我们
(AELSWITH) God save us.

563
00:41:28,160 --> 00:41:30,242
这是为了证明自己不怕痛
To show that they aren't afraid.

564
00:41:30,400 --> 00:41:34,325
连自己都能下得了手，你想想他们会怎么对付撒克逊人
If they can inflict pain on themselves, think what they can do to a Saxon.

565
00:41:34,480 --> 00:41:37,211
我相信我们对他们的了解会与日俱增
(ALFRED) We will understand them more by the day, I'm sure.

566
00:41:37,360 --> 00:41:40,842
丹麦人乌特雷德已经答应为我效力一年
Uhtred of the Danes has promised me a year of his service.

567
00:41:42,800 --> 00:41:44,245
是吗
Is that so?

568
00:41:44,400 --> 00:41:45,845
是的
It is.

569
00:41:46,000 --> 00:41:48,606
他的责任就是让我们的战士了解
It will be his responsibility to show our warriors

570
00:41:48,760 --> 00:41:50,410
丹麦人是如何迎战的
how the Danes approach battle,

571
00:41:50,600 --> 00:41:53,649
还有盾墙的布阵之法
the construction of their shield wall, and the like.

572
00:41:53,800 --> 00:41:55,768
大人 恕我冒昧的说一句
Lord, if I may,

573
00:41:55,920 --> 00:42:00,801
这浑球还不过是个毛头小子, 你指望他来教我打仗?
The arseling here is barely a man, you expect him to teach me to fight?

574
00:42:00,960 --> 00:42:03,725
利奥弗里克, 我可没指望他教你什么
Leofric, I expect him to teach you nothing.

575
00:42:04,440 --> 00:42:07,842
练兵时你尽管拿棍子抽他
Whip him with staves in practise by all means.

576
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:09,365
好的 大人
(LEOFRIC) Thank you, lord.

577
00:42:09,520 --> 00:42:10,931
但是
But,

578
00:42:11,320 --> 00:42:13,129
但我手下那些普通兵士,
our lesser men,

579
00:42:13,280 --> 00:42:15,567
若他们能摸透丹麦人的门道,
if they can know what a Dane knows,

580
00:42:16,480 --> 00:42:20,007
恐惧就会被知识驱散
fear can be expelled with knowledge,

581
00:42:20,400 --> 00:42:22,971
不管敌人的牙有多利
regardless how sharp their teeth.

582
00:42:36,520 --> 00:42:38,329
你今晚没吃东西
You didn't eat tonight.

583
00:42:38,480 --> 00:42:40,562
吃了也只会吐出来
I'd only throw it up.

584
00:42:41,440 --> 00:42:43,010
一年?
A year?

585
00:42:43,200 --> 00:42:44,645


586
00:42:45,240 --> 00:42:48,050
现在是定了一年, 说不定就是一辈子
It starts with a year and becomes a lifetime.

587
00:42:49,440 --> 00:42:50,805
他还给你许了门亲事?
And he offered you a wife?

588
00:42:50,960 --> 00:42:52,291
我不需要娶妻
I have no need of a wife.

589
00:42:52,440 --> 00:42:54,522
但你却宣誓要去杀丹麦人
Instead you swore an oath to kill Danes.

590
00:42:54,680 --> 00:42:56,842
你知道我这么做的原因
You know my reasons.

591
00:42:58,160 --> 00:43:00,561
我们一直住在王宫里
We have been living in a palace.

592
00:43:01,520 --> 00:43:03,284
要是你在战场上
What happens if you find yourself

593
00:43:03,440 --> 00:43:06,683
碰上了小拉格纳, 怎么办?
facing young Ragnar in battle?

594
00:43:10,520 --> 00:43:12,204
那就和他打
We fight.

595
00:43:40,040 --> 00:43:41,371
她在哪儿?
Where is she?

596
00:43:41,520 --> 00:43:44,888
- 今早一直没听到她的动静 - 她走不远的
- I haven't heard her all morning. - She'll not be far.

597
00:43:45,240 --> 00:43:46,765
好了,我们快要出发了
Well, we're about to leave.

598
00:43:46,920 --> 00:43:48,684
我看到了
I can see.

599
00:43:49,840 --> 00:43:51,410
我随后就来
I'll follow.

600
00:43:58,880 --> 00:44:02,202


601
00:44:05,960 --> 00:44:07,291


602
00:44:26,400 --> 00:44:28,050
布丽达!
(UHTRED) Bridal

603
00:44:37,120 --> 00:44:39,009
布丽达!
Bridal

604
00:44:51,400 --> 00:44:53,562
布丽达!
Bridal

605
00:45:00,680 --> 00:45:02,011
布丽达?
Bdda?

606
00:45:12,840 --> 00:45:14,842
几乎快成形了
Almost a child.

607
00:45:18,800 --> 00:45:20,882
- 你知道吗? - 嗯?
- You knew? - Hm?

608
00:45:21,320 --> 00:45:23,163
你知道自己有身孕?
That you were carrying?

609
00:45:29,080 --> 00:45:30,570
不知道
(BRIDA) No.

610
00:45:31,120 --> 00:45:33,361
你在梦里没有看到吗,
You didn't see it in your dreams,

611
00:45:33,520 --> 00:45:35,807
你喝了蘑菇麦酒的时候
when you drank the mushroom ale.

612
00:45:39,640 --> 00:45:40,971


613
00:45:42,320 --> 00:45:43,810
我来埋了它
I'll bury it.

614
00:45:46,520 --> 00:45:49,649
我们一起埋 这是逝去的征兆
We will bury it. It is a sign of a passing.

615
00:45:57,800 --> 00:46:01,122
- 并肩而立! - 盾牌向前!
- Stand together! - (UHTRED) Shields front!

616
00:46:01,280 --> 00:46:02,964
举起盾牌! 盾牌靠拢!
(LEOFRIC) Shields up! (UHTRED) Shields together!

617
00:46:03,760 --> 00:46:06,206
- 盯住他们的眼睛! - 靠紧些! 坚不可摧!
- Look them in the eye! - Closer together! Unbreakable!

618
00:46:06,360 --> 00:46:08,761
准备好了吗? 准备好了!
Are we ready? Yeah!

619
00:46:08,920 --> 00:46:11,241
- 我说,准备好了吗? - 前进!
- I said, are we ready? - Forward!

620
00:46:11,400 --> 00:46:13,687
准备好了!
Yeah!

621
00:46:14,480 --> 00:46:17,927
- 杀了这些混蛋! - 并肩而立!
- Kill the bastards! - Stand together!

622
00:46:18,120 --> 00:46:21,044


623
00:46:22,560 --> 00:46:24,005


624
00:46:24,800 --> 00:46:26,245
盾牌靠拢!
Shields together!

625
00:46:26,400 --> 00:46:30,405
用盾猛砸他们! 盾是我们的护甲, 也是我们的武器!
We hammer them with our shields! They are our defence and our weapon!

626
00:46:30,560 --> 00:46:32,244
把他们撞倒在地!
We knock them off their feet!

627
00:46:32,400 --> 00:46:33,845
我们就是一堵墙!
We are a wall!

628
00:46:34,040 --> 00:46:38,170


629
00:46:40,360 --> 00:46:41,930
冲!
Charge! 

630
00:46:42,120 --> 00:46:45,886


631
00:46:53,120 --> 00:46:54,485
两排盾墙交锋之前,
Before the two walls meet,

632
00:46:55,240 --> 00:46:59,325
前三排士兵必须协同配合, 筑起一道高耸的盾墙
the first three rows of men act together, to create a tall shield wall.

633
00:46:59,480 --> 00:47:03,326
第一排蹲低, 护住下腹和双腿
First row crouches lower, protecting the lower body and legs.

634
00:47:03,480 --> 00:47:07,405
第二排前伸, 护住上身
The second row reaches forward, protecting the upper body.

635
00:47:07,560 --> 00:47:12,521
第三排压上, 护住所有人的头顶
The third row leans in, protecting the head of all rows of men.

636
00:47:12,680 --> 00:47:14,409
举盾!
Shields up.

637
00:47:15,880 --> 00:47:17,370
盾牌靠拢!
Shields together!

638
00:47:18,600 --> 00:47:20,443
立盾墙!
Shield Wall!

639
00:47:25,080 --> 00:47:26,650
不赖嘛, 浑球
I like it, arseling.

640
00:47:27,240 --> 00:47:28,924
真的不错
I do.

641
00:47:29,720 --> 00:47:32,326
现在, 杀了那帮混蛋!
Now, kill the bastards!

642
00:47:32,520 --> 00:47:34,329


643
00:47:36,360 --> 00:47:39,648


644
00:47:52,800 --> 00:47:54,131
这些财物不是我的,
(BRIDA) The wealth is not mine,

645
00:47:55,520 --> 00:47:57,682
是无畏的拉格纳大人的
it belongs to Lord Ragnar, the fearless.

646
00:47:58,560 --> 00:48:01,131
你最好离我远点
You will do well to leave me alone.

647
00:48:01,280 --> 00:48:03,567
你是布丽达?
(MAN) Are you Brida?

648
00:48:03,880 --> 00:48:05,644
谁在问?
Who asks?

649
00:48:10,400 --> 00:48:13,131
- 布丽达 - 她怎么了?
- Brida. - What of her?

650
00:48:14,440 --> 00:48:16,602
我不是先知,
I'm no seer,

651
00:48:16,760 --> 00:48:18,364
但我看得出她过得不开心
but I'd say she's unhappy.

652
00:48:19,880 --> 00:48:23,248
她更喜欢和丹麦人待在一起, 不喜欢撒克逊人,
She prefers the company of Danes to Saxons,

653
00:48:23,400 --> 00:48:24,731
这没什么问题
nothing wrong in that.

654
00:48:25,720 --> 00:48:27,484
她跟的那些撒克逊人不是好货
She's been with the wrong Saxons.

655
00:48:28,040 --> 00:48:31,249
- 丹麦人对生活有股劲 - 谁没有呢?
- The Danes have a hunger for life. - Don't we all?

656
00:48:32,240 --> 00:48:33,844
阿尔弗雷德...
Alfred...

657
00:48:35,640 --> 00:48:37,802
他是个认真的人
He's serious.

658
00:48:38,160 --> 00:48:40,686
虔诚的混蛋
A pious bastard.

659
00:48:40,840 --> 00:48:42,444
你可以不喜欢他,
Dislike him, by all means,

660
00:48:42,600 --> 00:48:45,206
但千万别小看他
but never underestimate him.

661
00:48:45,600 --> 00:48:47,250
他心狠手辣,
He's ruthless,

662
00:48:47,400 --> 00:48:50,131
而且脑子好使,
and the man thinks,

663
00:48:50,280 --> 00:48:52,442
这一点你我都比不上
which is more than you or I could do.

664
00:48:52,600 --> 00:48:54,443
战士利奥弗里克,
Leofric the warrior,

665
00:48:55,160 --> 00:48:56,491
我能坐你旁边吗?
may I sit with you?

666
00:48:56,640 --> 00:48:58,324
不行
No, you may not.

667
00:48:58,480 --> 00:49:00,767
修道院的僧侣们知道你跑出来了吗?
Do the monks know you're missing?

668
00:49:02,000 --> 00:49:05,686
乌特雷德, 这是埃塞尔沃尔德, 又一个浑球
Uhtred, this is Aethelwold, another arseling.

669
00:49:06,520 --> 00:49:10,286
- 国王的侄子 - 不, 我不是国王的侄子
- Nephew of the king. - No, I am not the nephew of the king.

670
00:49:10,440 --> 00:49:13,569
我才是国王
I am the king.

671
00:49:14,280 --> 00:49:15,770
但阿尔弗雷德喜欢装模作样,
But Alfred likes to pretend,

672
00:49:15,920 --> 00:49:18,651
每个浑蛋都乐意配合他演这出戏, 哈哈
and every bastard appears to be happy with the lie. Heh, heh.

673
00:49:21,240 --> 00:49:23,641
- 咱们在说什么? - 阿尔弗雷德
- What are we talking about? - Alfred.

674
00:49:23,800 --> 00:49:26,531
他不让我上战场, 我跟你说过吗?
He will not allow me to fight. Have I told you that?

675
00:49:26,680 --> 00:49:28,330
- 说过很多次了 - 反正是真的
- Many times. - Well, it's true.

676
00:49:28,480 --> 00:49:30,130
他就是不让我打仗
He will not allow me to fight.

677
00:49:30,280 --> 00:49:33,363
利奥弗里克, 勇士, 我想请你
I would like you, warrior Leofric,

678
00:49:33,520 --> 00:49:37,844
教我怎么打仗, 我来教你怎么...
to teach me how to fight and I shall teach you how to...

679
00:49:38,000 --> 00:49:41,083
- 继续说 - 你可别忘了付钱
- (LEOFRIC) Go on. - You will not forget to pay for this.

680
00:49:41,960 --> 00:49:43,405
我有忘过吗?
Have I ever?

681
00:49:43,560 --> 00:49:45,528
有过一两次
Once or twice.

682
00:49:55,880 --> 00:49:57,928
阿尔弗雷德有次被抓到跟修女鬼混
Alfred was caught humping a nun once.

683
00:49:58,120 --> 00:49:59,485


684
00:50:00,120 --> 00:50:03,841
我真该一刀捅了他的喉咙
(AETHELWOLD) What I ought to do is slit his gizzard. Unh!

685
00:50:04,000 --> 00:50:06,765
这话要是让别人听见, 小子, 你就得上绞架
(LEOFRIC) Say that to anyone but me, boy, and you'll be hanged.

686
00:50:06,920 --> 00:50:09,366
你这是在伤害皇室血脉
(AETHELWOLD) You are hurting royalty.

687
00:50:09,560 --> 00:50:11,289


688
00:50:12,680 --> 00:50:15,047
你应该庆幸阿尔弗雷德没杀你
You are lucky Alfred hasn't had you killed.

689
00:50:15,200 --> 00:50:17,601
天主不会允许他那样做
God will not allow him.

690
00:50:18,240 --> 00:50:19,969
我挺喜欢天主的
I like God.

691
00:50:20,680 --> 00:50:22,489


692
00:50:25,120 --> 00:50:27,248


693
00:50:41,240 --> 00:50:43,242


694
00:50:48,680 --> 00:50:50,250
银子
Silver.

695
00:50:50,960 --> 00:50:52,405
对
Yes.

696
00:50:52,560 --> 00:50:54,210
为什么?
Why?

697
00:50:56,160 --> 00:50:58,925
- 你要离开我 - 你喝多了?
- You leaving me. - Are you drunk?

698
00:51:00,520 --> 00:51:02,409
也许有一点
Maybe a little.

699
00:51:02,560 --> 00:51:05,245
我们把这些银子给小拉格纳
We will give the silver to young Ragnar.

700
00:51:06,640 --> 00:51:08,290
明天
Tomorrow.

701
00:51:08,440 --> 00:51:10,408
黄昏时分
Dusk.

702
00:51:12,360 --> 00:51:13,725
他来了
He's here.

703
00:51:14,920 --> 00:51:17,082
我们可以告诉他实情,
We can tell him the truth,

704
00:51:17,920 --> 00:51:20,491
然后加入拉格纳和他的人马
and we can join Ragnar and his men.

705
00:51:27,640 --> 00:51:32,965
我需要的人, 要被天主、职责、土地、威塞克斯本身所束缚
I need men bound to me by God, by duty, by the land, by Wessex itself.

706
00:51:33,680 --> 00:51:37,207
我想再次向乌特雷德提出联姻的事
I would again like to put to Uhtred the prospect of marriage.

707
00:51:37,360 --> 00:51:40,170
- 嫁给我的教女? - 是的, 米尔德丝
- To my goddaughter? - To Mildrith, yes.

708
00:51:41,240 --> 00:51:43,641
这确实能让他与这片土地紧密相连
Well, it would certainly bind him to the land,

709
00:51:43,800 --> 00:51:45,768
也间接地与教会和天主紧密相连
and indirectly to the church, to God.

710
00:51:45,920 --> 00:51:48,685
- 这是对他的考验 - 没错
- It would test him. - It would.

711
00:51:48,840 --> 00:51:51,286
你还是愿意支持吗?
You would be in favour still?

712
00:51:51,440 --> 00:51:52,851
当然
Of course.

713
00:51:53,000 --> 00:51:54,604
为了威塞克斯, 什么都值得
Anything for Wessex.

714
00:52:08,840 --> 00:52:11,810
成为乌特雷德 拉格纳松这个身份是不错的
Uhtred Ragnarson is a good man to be.

715
00:52:13,480 --> 00:52:14,970
看着我
Look at me.

716
00:52:15,120 --> 00:52:17,122
你什么都不欠阿尔弗雷德
You owe Alfred nothing.

717
00:52:17,280 --> 00:52:20,329
在他眼里, 你的誓言一文不值, 因为你是个异教徒
To him, your word means nothing, you are a pagan.

718
00:52:20,480 --> 00:52:22,164
求你了
Please.

719
00:52:30,960 --> 00:52:35,761
乌特雷德 拉格纳松永远成不了贝班堡的乌特雷德
Uhtred Ragnarson can never become Uhtred of Bebbanburg.

720
00:52:38,920 --> 00:52:40,490
永远不会
Never.

721
00:52:42,480 --> 00:52:44,528


722
00:52:50,920 --> 00:52:52,843
是你杀了我父亲吗?
Did you kill my father?

723
00:52:53,880 --> 00:52:55,211
你还用问?
You need to ask?

724
00:52:55,360 --> 00:52:58,170
是你杀了我的家人吗?
Did you kill my family?

725
00:52:58,320 --> 00:52:59,651
他没有
He didn't.

726
00:52:59,800 --> 00:53:02,246
我和乌特雷德说话
I am speaking with Uhtred.

727
00:53:04,800 --> 00:53:08,407
我不会问第二遍
I won't ask a second time.

728
00:53:13,040 --> 00:53:15,771
如果你以为是我杀了咱们的父亲,
If you believe that I would kill our father,

729
00:53:15,920 --> 00:53:18,002
咱们的母亲,
our mother,

730
00:53:18,160 --> 00:53:19,969
还有咱们的家人...
and our family...

731
00:53:23,280 --> 00:53:25,442
那就来报仇吧
Take your revenge.

732
00:53:33,320 --> 00:53:34,970
我就知道
I knew it.

733
00:53:36,040 --> 00:53:37,644
我就知道
I knew it.

734
00:53:38,880 --> 00:53:40,370
我必须确认一下, 但我就知道
I had to be sure, I knew it.

735
00:53:47,360 --> 00:53:49,362
是基尔坦干的
It was Kjartan.

736
00:53:49,760 --> 00:53:51,967
是基尔坦发动了袭击, 放的火
Kjartan attacked and set the fire.

737
00:53:52,120 --> 00:53:55,010
- 要是能救他们, 我们早救了 - 我就知道
- If we could have saved them, we would. - I knew it.

738
00:53:55,160 --> 00:53:57,322
那些话我一个字都没信
I didn't believe a word I was hearing.

739
00:53:57,480 --> 00:54:00,006
拉格纳的财富都在我们手里
We have Ragnar's wealth.

740
00:54:00,160 --> 00:54:02,083
我们一直替你保管着
We kept it for you.

741
00:54:03,760 --> 00:54:07,321
- 布丽达, 都长大成人了 - 嘿嘿嘿
- Bride. A fully grown woman now. - Heh, heh, heh.

742
00:54:13,560 --> 00:54:17,007
这一刻我在梦里见过太多次了
I've seen this moment in my dreams so many times.

743
00:54:19,880 --> 00:54:24,090
基尔坦的说法是英格兰人在你的鼓励下起来反抗咱们的父亲,
So Kjartan's story is that the English rose against our father,

744
00:54:24,240 --> 00:54:26,607

encouraged by you.

745
00:54:27,960 --> 00:54:31,282
他声称自己已经为那些杀手报了仇
He claims to have revenged himself for the killers.

746
00:54:32,360 --> 00:54:34,488
你有相信过他吗?
Did you ever believe him?

747
00:54:35,040 --> 00:54:36,405


748
00:54:36,560 --> 00:54:38,289
从没信过
Never.

749
00:54:39,040 --> 00:54:40,804
但他现在是基尔坦大人了
But he is Lord Kjartan now.

750
00:54:40,960 --> 00:54:44,885
手下的人是咱们的三倍, 还有乌巴撑腰
He has three times the men, and the ear of Ubba.

751
00:54:47,680 --> 00:54:49,170
嗯
Hm.

752
00:54:49,840 --> 00:54:52,923
我要杀他, 得好好谋划
When I kill him, it will need to be planned.

753
00:54:53,560 --> 00:54:55,528
是我们一起杀他
When we kill him.

754
00:54:56,560 --> 00:54:59,325
- 这会很危险 - 但必须去做
- It will be dangerous. - It must be done.

755
00:54:59,480 --> 00:55:01,960
拉格纳, 我们与你同在
Ragnar, we're with you.

756
00:55:03,720 --> 00:55:06,291
那你们愿意随我出航?
Then you will sail with me?

757
00:55:08,320 --> 00:55:09,890
愿意
I Will.

758
00:55:11,320 --> 00:55:14,085
我已向阿尔弗雷德宣过誓
I have sworn to Alfred.

759
00:55:14,680 --> 00:55:16,409
那算不了什么
It means nothing.

760
00:55:19,360 --> 00:55:21,681
好吧你既然已经发过誓...
Well, if you have sworn...

761
00:55:24,080 --> 00:55:26,401
就得说话算数
Then you must keep your word.

762
00:55:36,960 --> 00:55:40,009
这份复仇对我来说, 如同水一般不可或缺
I need this revenge like I need water.

763
00:55:40,920 --> 00:55:44,322
时机成熟之时, 我发誓我一定与你并肩
When the time is right, I swear I will be with you.

764
00:55:45,240 --> 00:55:47,129
我知道
I know.

765
00:55:55,520 --> 00:55:58,490
真不敢相信我就要放你离开了
I can't believe I'm about to let you go.

766
00:55:59,400 --> 00:56:01,164
就这么失去你
Lose you.

767
00:56:04,120 --> 00:56:06,805
你已经成为我一半的生命
You have been half my life.

768
00:56:09,400 --> 00:56:11,846
全部的疯狂
All of my madness.

769
00:56:22,400 --> 00:56:24,164
过的开心点
Be happy.

770
00:56:52,000 --> 00:56:54,401
她走了吧?
(LEOFRIC) I take it she has gone then?

771
00:56:57,320 --> 00:57:00,324
我猜阿尔弗雷德是让你选择留下的原因
I'm guessing that's it's Alfred that kept you here.

772
00:57:01,600 --> 00:57:03,728
我为了一件锁甲和一顶头盔
I sold myself.

773
00:57:04,920 --> 00:57:07,491
出卖了自己
For a mail coat and helmet.

774
00:57:08,080 --> 00:57:11,084
我们都是这样, 把自己出卖出去
That's what we do, we sell ourselves.

775
00:57:15,280 --> 00:57:17,009
今年这一年,
This year,

776
00:57:17,400 --> 00:57:21,086
你要为阿尔弗雷德付出的, 和锁甲没关系
what you've giving to Alfred, it's not about a mail coat.

777
00:57:21,240 --> 00:57:23,163
和你自己有关
It's about you.

778
00:57:23,640 --> 00:57:26,120
这混蛋很聪明, 我没说错吧?
The bastard thinks, didn't I say?

779
00:57:30,360 --> 00:57:33,011
他要的不只是一年的效力
He wants more than a year's service.

780
00:57:33,480 --> 00:57:36,484
他要你帮他夺回英格兰
He wants you to help take back England.

781
00:57:36,880 --> 00:57:38,644
整个英格兰
All of England.

782
00:57:40,760 --> 00:57:44,162
当然, 等一年期满, 你可以回丹麦人那边去
Of course, when the year's up, you could go back to the Danes.

783
00:57:44,920 --> 00:57:47,890
那样我至少有机会杀了你
That would at least give me the chance to kill you.

784
00:57:50,440 --> 00:57:52,283
但你会成为什么?
But what would you be?

785
00:57:53,920 --> 00:57:55,843
你又会是谁?
Who would you be?
